The article discusses the State of the Union Fact Sheet released by the White House in 2014. The fact sheet outlines the key executive actions that the President plans to take in 2014 to expand opportunity for all Americans. The actions focus on areas such as middle class security and opportunity at work, jobs and economic opportunity, schools and education opportunity, and securing a safe and sound housing finance system. Some of the specific actions mentioned include raising the minimum wage for federal contract workers, creating a new retirement savings account called "myRA," launching new manufacturing institutes, increasing fuel efficiency for trucks, connecting students to technology in schools, and making college more affordable. The fact sheet also mentions the President's plans to work with Congress on various issues, including extending emergency unemployment insurance, raising the minimum wage, and reforming the immigration system.